<br>
Mages WERE one of the classes that vi touted as being able to solo.  Saying otherwise is foolish, get your facts straight.  Is EQ a group orientated game ? yes.  Did they intend for some classes to be able to solo, YES, they said so themselves.  Regardless of their intentions, many classes that VI themselves didnt regard as solo classes have envolved into them due to spell lines / abilites that have been handed out.<br>
<br>
For those of you who say pop isnt meant to be soloable, please tell that to the bards, wizards, druids, rangers, sks, shaman, necros &amp; enchanters that I see soloing in pov every day!  That or get a clue cause youre clearly wrong &amp; dont know wtf youre talking about!<br>
<br>
Maybe only 3/15 classes get slows, but 8/15 get to solo in pov.  Any effective group in pop has a slower, anyone who says different is nuts.<br>
<br>
The fact of the matter is pop gimped mage solo power by rewarding classes that can mitigate damage through some means, mages mitigate damage with... uhm.. gate &amp; thats why we are far less powerful than we have ever been.  Anyone who cant see this fact is fooling themselves.  This is just the latest case of vi yanking mages around &amp; basically redefining their abilities in regards to how to play - i'm sure it was unintentional too, which is the really sad thing about this.  It doesnt impact me a ton because i've got a lot of friends - but I know a lotta people who play mages like really late at night/odd hours &amp; they have NEVER grouped...and now they are screwed completly since they can a) no longer solo &amp; b) either play at odd hours so cant get regular groups going, dont have contacts made to get into groups or a combination of the two.  I know several people who basically dont play anymore because of this &amp; I think its wrong.<br>
<br>
